# Autorec : Autoencoder meets Collaborative Filtering
***Last edit : 30 June 2019***

(Sedhain, S., Menon, A. K., Sanner, S., & Xie, L. (2015, May). 

[AutoRec : Autoencoders meet collaborative filtering](http://users.cecs.anu.edu.au/~akmenon/papers/autorec/autorec-paper.pdf). 
In Proceedings of the 24th International Conference on World Wide Web (pp. 111-112). ACM.)

# **! Important !**

The purpose of this repository and `Autorec/ml-1m` test, was to check whether original implementation of autorec, gives similar scores for all user (difference less than 10e-4). This issue happened when the rating is normalized. (To prove whether there's implementation mistakes on the GDP-Autorec)

# Contents
- data : contains dataset to use in training  
    - ml-1m : original movielens 1m dataset
- log : contains training result stored in single folder named after training timestamp.
- test : contains jupyter notebook used in testing the trained models
<!-- ---------------------------------------- -->
- `AutoRec.py` : source code for Autorec
- `data_preprocessor.py` : preprocess data before fed into for Autorec
- `logger.py` : log training result and save models
- `main.py` : script to run training 

# How to run
    python3 main.py

# Preparing 
## Installing dependencies 

    pip3 install -r requirements.txt

# Training
## How to change hyper parameter
There are several ways to do this :
1. Open `main.py` and change the args parser default value
2. run `main.py` with arguments required.

